    tag: "FINANCIAL_RISK_MODELING",
    title: "Business Context Engine",
    short: "Translates technical vulnerability scores into precise financial exposure metrics with Bayesian risk modeling and ROI-based remediation prioritization.",
    technical:
      "The Business Context Engine (BCE) implements a structured 5-phase data pipeline to enrich technical vulnerability data with business context and financial risk metrics.\n\n**1. Context Lookup and Mapping Creation**\n- Executes PostgreSQL queries to pull business context mappings from bce_resource_mappings, business_applications, and business_units tables\n- Compiles results into an in-memory lookup dictionary keyed by ResourceARN for fast access\n- SQL Join: SELECT m.resource_arn, a.app_name, u.unit_name, u.criticality, a.is_pci, a.is_kvkk FROM bce_resource_mappings m JOIN business_applications a ON m.app_id = a.id JOIN business_units u ON a.unit_id = u.id\n\n**2. Graph Node Enrichment & Bayesian Risk Calculations**\n- Traverses active NetworkX/Neo4j graph representation, injecting business metadata fields\n- Risk Score Recalculation: Risk_New = Risk_Orig × (1.0 + BU_Criticality/10.0 + 0.5_PCI + 0.4_KVKK/GDPR)\n- Bayesian Age-Decay EPSS for zero-days: Effective_EPSS = max(EPSS, 0.42 × e^(decay_coefficient × Age))\n- Adjusted Node Risk with 0.1 floor: max(0.1, Base_Risk × (0.2 + 0.8 × Effective_EPSS))\n- Zero-Day qualification: If CVSS ≥ 9.0 and EPSS < 0.10, Effective_EPSS forced to 0.65 baseline\n\n**3. Attack Path Analytics & Length Inflation**\n- Capped Edge TDS based on deployed controls (WAF, SG, MFA, KMS): TDS_Network = min(1.2, Σ TDS_components), TDS_Identity = min(1.8, Σ TDS_components)\n- Harmonic Mean Exploitability (no length bias): Harmonic_Mean = k / Σ(1/risk_i)\n- Length Inflation with log-based saturation: Length_Inflation = log_2(1 + n)^0.8\n- Criticality Calculation: Criticality = Financial_Blast_Radius × (Harmonic_Mean / (1 + Σ TDS_e)) × Length_Inflation\n\n**4. Choke Point Discovery & Remediation Net ROI**\n- Choke Point Importance Score (CPIS): CPIS = Σ Path_Exploitability × UAEU (Unique Asset Exposure Union)\n- Net ROI Evaluation: Net_ROI = Risk_Saved(UAEU) - (Effort_Hours × Role_Rate × Automation_Multiplier)\n- Crown Jewel Exception: Marks recommendations eligible even if Net ROI negative when asset is PCI-DSS classified or liability ≥ $1.0M\n\n**5. Dynamic Storytelling, Feedback & Exclusions**\n- Compiles dynamic narrative stories (Turkish and English) mapping exact exploit paths or falling back to absent phrases\n- User rejection persistence to PostgreSQL with IGNORED_RECOMMENDATION tagging (is_ignored = true)\n- 2-hop sub-graph invalidation triggered on recommendation rejection\n- Expired cleaner background sweeper periodically scans PostgreSQL, deletes expired exclusions, removes matching tags in Neo4j\n\n**Configuration Reference**\n- financials.base_cost_per_record: Base cost per exposed data record (default: $200)\n- flat_regulatory_penalties.pci_dss: Flat penalty for PCI violations (default: $250,000)\n- roles.l3_security_engineer_hourly_rate: Hourly rate for manual remediation costs (default: $250)\n- bce_tenant_configs.cycle_resolution_strategy: 'oldest_first' or 'least_locked' for deadlock escalation",
    business:
      "**Transform 1,000 Cloud Alerts Into 1 Strategic Action**\n\nTraditional vulnerability scanners generate thousands of high-severity alerts based solely on static technical scores like CVSS 9.8, completely lacking business context. This alert fatigue paradox forces security teams to spend weeks patching minor, non-critical exposures while high-value data reservoirs remain unprotected. The Business Context Engine resolves this crisis by translating abstract technical scores into concrete financial metrics—regulatory fines, legal penalties, data recovery costs, and SLA liabilities—providing executive leadership with clear dollar-based risk visibility.\n\nInstead of overwhelming teams with endless vulnerability lists, BCE filters background noise to recommend a Single Point of Remediation (SPR): the single most critical Choke Point that secures maximum sensitive data volume with minimal operational effort. The engine calculates manual remediation labor costs (engineering hours × role-based rates) and compares against automated alternatives, enabling data-driven resource allocation decisions with clear ROI demonstration to board stakeholders. Automatic regulatory alignment maps security posture findings to PCI-DSS, GDPR, and regional compliance mandates, maintaining continuous compliance while reducing audit preparation overhead.\n\n**Financial Blast Radius Model:** (Record_Count × $200 × Class_Weight) + Flat_Penalties + Replacement_Cost\n**Real Example:** 1,000 customer records (PII) with KVKK exposure = (1000 × $200 × 1.8) + $50,000 (KVKK) + $5,000 (RDS) = $415,000 total exposure\n\n**Crown Jewel Exception Rule:** Automatically overrides standard labor cost logic when target network contains sensitive data or exposure liability exceeds $1,000,000, triggering immediate security isolation regardless of ROI calculations.",
