    short: "Dual-strategy automated security posture remediation with SDK-based immediate fixes and Terraform IaC workflows.",
    technical:
      "The remediation module implements a comprehensive dual-strategy framework combining immediate AWS SDK-based remediation and Infrastructure as Code (IaC) approaches using Terraform. The SDK pipeline (autofix_pipeline/) provides synchronous remediation for 16+ AWS resource types including EC2, IAM, S3, RDS, Lambda, Load Balancers, Security Groups, and CloudTrail, with SSM Automation integration and direct boto3 fallback. The FastAPI microservice architecture decouples request ingestion from AWS execution using Redis job tracking with UUIDv4 job IDs, status lifecycle management (pending → in_progress → completed/failed), and 1-hour TTL for automatic cleanup. Pydantic validation ensures input sanitization with HTTP 422 error responses for invalid actions. Background task execution via FastAPI BackgroundTasks enables immediate HTTP 201 responses (< 50ms) while async workers execute boto3 API calls. Structured JSON audit logging captures timestamp, level, job_id, bucket, and action for SIEM collection. The Terraform engine (terraform_engine.py) generates HCL from live AWS state, supports remote backends (S3 + DynamoDB locking), implements STS AssumeRole for cross-account delegation, and features automatic state backup/rollback on failure. The 10-layer rollback engine includes aioboto3 integration, Tenacity retry with exponential backoff, Pydantic v2 validation, pluggable idempotency backends, per-service circuit breakers, two-phase commit state persistence, and graceful shutdown. The choke point analysis engine identifies high-ROI remediation targets using NetworkX betweenness centrality computation, risk mass accumulation with centrality boosting, MITRE ATT&CK compliance mapping for 18 resource types, and safety assessment that blocks root account modifications. The validation engine provides 7-layer confidence scoring (THEORETICAL_ONLY through VERIFIED_ATTACK_PATH), layered validator execution with ThreadPoolExecutor, and IAM simulation via AWS iam:SimulatePrincipalPolicy.\n\n**Key Technical Capabilities:**\n- **Dual-Strategy Execution:** Immediate SDK remediation for urgent fixes + Terraform IaC for auditable infrastructure changes.\n- **16+ AWS Resource Types:** EC2, IAM, S3, RDS, Lambda, ALB/NLB/CLB, Security Groups, CloudTrail, API Gateway, CloudFront, VPC, Target Groups, Listeners, ASG, DNS Records, AMI.\n- **10-Layer Rollback Engine:** aioboto3 async operations, Tenacity exponential backoff, Pydantic v2 validation, pluggable state stores (DynamoDB/PostgreSQL), per-service circuit breakers, two-phase commit, trace ID propagation.\n- **Choke Point Analysis:** NetworkX betweenness centrality, risk mass calculation with centrality boost (base_mass * (1.0 + (centrality_score * 5.0))), MITRE ATT&CK mapping, safety assessment blocking high-risk operations.\n- **Terraform IaC Engine:** HCL generation from live state, remote backend support (S3 + DynamoDB), STS AssumeRole cross-account delegation, automatic state backup/rollback, HCL syntax validation in sandbox.\n- **Validation Engine:** 7-layer confidence hierarchy, layered validators (GenericPathValidator, RuntimeEvidenceValidator, IAMSimulationValidator, ActiveTestValidator), parallel validation with ThreadPoolExecutor (max 5 workers).\n- **Enterprise Resilience:** Token bucket rate limiting (5.0 rate, 10.0 capacity), per-service circuit breakers (iam, rds, s3, ec2, cloudtrail, elbv2, dynamodb, kms, lambda, eks, ecs, wafv2, apigateway, cloudfront, sqs), exponential backoff with jitter.\n- **Safety & Compliance:** Dry-run mode, backup record creation before all changes, automatic rollback on failure, audit logging to immutable files, MITRE ATT&CK compliance mapping.\n\n**Execution Flow Diagram:**\n```\n[Threat Event Ingestion]\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Phase 1: JWT/Secret Signature Check  │\n│  - HMAC-SHA256 validation            │\n│  - Abort HTTP 401 on failure         │\n└──────────────────┬───────────────────┘\n                   │\n                   ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Phase 2: Redis Deduplication       │\n│  - Key: dedup:<action_hash>          │\n│  - SET NX EX 300 (5-min cooldown)    │\n│  - Discard if key exists             │\n└──────────────────┬───────────────────┘\n                   │\n                   ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Phase 3: Severity Routing          │\n│  - Critical → PagerDuty Webhook      │\n│  - High → Slack #slack-alerts         │\n│  - Medium/Low → Slack #monitoring    │\n│  - Load remediation.yaml playbook    │\n└──────────────────┬───────────────────┘\n                   │\n                   ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Phase 4: Rate Limiter & Execution   │\n│  - Token Bucket: 5 ops/sec limit     │\n│  ├─► mock_mode=true → In-Memory Sim  │\n│  └─► mock_mode=false → AWS SDK v2    │\n└──────────────────┬───────────────────┘\n                   │\n                   ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Phase 5: Circuit Breaker Eval      │\n│  - Monitor Neo4j/AWS API calls      │\n│  - Trip to OPEN after 5 failures    │\n│  - HALF-OPEN after 30s cooldown      │\n└──────────────────┬───────────────────┘\n                   │\n                   ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Phase 6: Excel Audit & S3 Upload    │\n│  - Generate Excel report            │\n│  - Upload to S3: kassandra-reports  │\n└──────────────────────────────────────┘\n```",
